# Mini Library Management System â€” Environment Example
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (local dev) or supply the keys via your hosting provider.
# Values listed here reflect the minimum contract locked in `docs/dev/spec/spec-final.md`.

# --- Supabase (required) ---
SUPABASE_URL="https://your-project.supabase.co"
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="supabase-anon-key"
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY="supabase-service-role-key"  # Keep server-only; never expose to client builds.

# --- Nuxt runtime configuration ---
# Canonical site URL used in emails and redirects.
NUXT_APP_SITE_URL="http://localhost:3000"
# Public Supabase settings shipped to the browser.
NUXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="${SUPABASE_URL}"
NUXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="${SUPABASE_ANON_KEY}"
# Default cover art used by seeds/UI fallbacks.
NUXT_APP_DEFAULT_COVER_URL="https://your-project.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/covers/default.webp"
# Comma-separated domains for remote images (mirrors nuxt.config.ts > image.domains once added).
NUXT_IMAGE_DOMAINS="your-project.supabase.co"

# --- OpenAI integration ---
OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
OPENAI_MODEL="gpt-4o-mini"

# --- Observability & analytics (optional but recommended) ---
# Uncomment and populate as integrations are configured.
# SENTRY_DSN=""
# LOGFLARE_SOURCE=""
# POSTHOG_API_KEY=""

# --- Testing & tooling ---
# Feature flag that enables the daily OpenAI canary test in CI (`true` / `false`).
NUXT_OPENAI_CANARY_ENABLED="false"
